text:
="preserve">Jana Andresíková (2 April 1941 – 19 October 2020) was a Czech actress. Andresíková was born in Kroměříž, Czech Republic. She was known for her roles in "The Young Man and Moby Dick" (1979), "Giorgino" (1994) and "Arabela" (1979–1981).
Andresíková died on 19 October 2020 from COVID-19 in Mělník, Czech Republic at the age of 79.
